Dr. Deborah Birx says anyone who dies with COVID-19 (regardless of other health issues) is counted as COVID death.

Worse, CDC doesn't require TESTS to confirm COVID before it's coded as COVID death.
If symptoms are present... that's enough. (April 7, 2020)
